  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6600.11 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-19.4B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+24.1B), dealers are currently in neutral hedging mode but poised to become active buyers on any dip toward 6590 or sellers on a push above 6605. The PIN regime with positive total GEX (+19.2B) suggests dealers will provide liquidity against directional moves, creating mean-reverting behavior within the 6590-6605 range. Watch for amplified volatility if we break below 6590 (dealers turn into momentum sellers) versus increased resistance and profit-taking above the 6605 wall where dealers dump shares.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to ping-pong between 6590-6605 with dealers smoothing out moves.",
